I'm so excited to be participating in Ink Blot Shop's New Release Hop!

You should have arrived here from wonderful @inkblotshop

The entire hop listing is at the bottom of this post.

Um, YES! I love Ink Blot Shop's release, especially the two sets I'm playing with:

💗 Hot & Cold Drinks*
💗 Sweet Times Sentiments 

I'm shakin' things up with my project. I have so many 6x6 paper pads so I decided to base my design based on the striped panel.  The coffee cups have been colored with copic markers. 

The shaker window is an upcycled stamp package sleeve.  #swipeforphoto I have so many of those sleeves jammed into a drawer.  I slide all my stamps + designer dies into the heavyweight sleeves but keep the packaging to reuse. When I use bumpier shaker embellishments I use the traditional method with foam tape.

*A portion of the sales (15%) of the Hot & Cold Drinks stamp set and the Citrus Squeeze Background stamp will be donated to the Write With Light Project for retail sales placed through May 31, 2023. The Write With Light Project is a nonprofit organization that raises money to improve the lives of those struggling with rare conditions. In 2023, in honor of a spunky heart warrior named Sunley, profits will go toward the Fontan Go Clinic at Texas Children’s Hospital. This will provide specialty care for anyone who has had a Fontan procedure. 

I can't wait to see how everyone was inspired by this awesome release.  A big thank you to Tifany for the invite!

A big thank you to @lawnfawn for sending me products from their Summer Release.  If you've been following me for the last 2 years'ish you might have heard me chat about my grandpup Kuma.  The new Yappy Birthday set was screaming for me to design a Gotcha Day card.  We'll be celebrating on July 7th.

The images were stamped on watercolor paper and colored with Zig Clean Color Real Brush Markers and their blender pen.  I combined these Lawn Fawn products:

💛 Yappy Birthday stamps + lawn cuts
💛 Simply Sentiments stamps*
💛 Magic Iris lawn cuts*
💛 Oliver’s Stitched ABC’s lawn cuts*
💛 Sunburst Backdrop*

*previously released 

I used the stitched circle from the Magic Iris set for the center 'ribbon' piece.  It works beautifully with the Sunburst Backdrop.  I decided to add the white embossed sentiment strip instead of trying to fit all those words in the center.

I'm so grateful that my girl adopted Kuma.  She is the sweetest pup #swipeforpic  They think that she was chained up most of her life in the state of Texas.  Her teeth were in horrific shape so she ended up having many extractions which causes her tongue to do that LOL. 

Any Washington State locals interested in more information about fostering or adopting, please check out @rescueunleashed  #adoptdontshop #adoptadog #fosteradog #homelessdogcrisis

Thanks to my friends at @waffleflowercrafts for sending me the 6x6 Grip Mat to try out.  They also included some other products including their gorgeous Sketched Hawthorn Bundle.

This is when I tell you that I want all the sizes😍 I used it specially for the stencil work on today's card. The Sketched Hawthorn Bundle comes with:

🌸 Sketched Hawthorn Stamp set
🌸 Sketched Hawthorn Matching Die
🌸 Sketched Hawthorn Foil Plate 
🌸 Sketched Hawthorn Coloring Stencil 

Each of the products are also available separately.

I stamped the Sketched Hawthorn image on an A2 panel and placed it centered - in the middle of the Grip Mat.  I l started the stencil work, making sure that I masked off any part of the stencil I wasn't working with. When I was finished stenciling the entire image, I gently peeled it off of the mat.  I ran the colored image through my die cutter.  I wanted to do a quick touch up on one portion of the bloom so placed it back onto the Grip Mat and did some quick ink blending.

I also added a layer to my design that features the gorgeous Tiny Diamonds Foil Plate.  The sentiment is from the Subsentiments Gift Diecut. All you have to do is clip and adhere!

So why use the Grip Mat? It eliminates the use of magnets and washi to adhere your panel/image in place. Use it in your Misti or other stamp positioner.  Use it on a glass mat - that's what I did for today's project.  Great for stenciling, ink blending, stamping - pretty much everything you do for a project. Easy to clean + Easy to store.

If you haven't watched Waffle Flower's videos on the Grip Mat, I highly recommend them.  There is an Introduction video that is 1 min and a 'Which Size is Right For You' video that is 12 min. I have them both linked in my blog post. #linkinbio  I'll be back next week with another project using the Grip Mat!

My girl and I spent the last couple of days on a road, Seattle to Wyoming. This is my second time and my daughter's first. Unfortunately, it was to go to a memorial service. My good friend recently lost her Dad. She and her family always make me feel so comfortable + welcome.

#swipeformorephotos 
1. Me and my Girl - Park City, MT 
2. Best back seat driver - Kuma! It definitely adds more time + coordination when you bring a pup.  She did great, the only other long road trip she's been on is Seattle to Portland.
3. Sheridan, WY Airbnb - #linkinbio We stayed at THE cutest place in Sheridan, WY. The kind that makes you want to redo your home. It's dog friendly! SUPER clean, hip and comfortable.  I would definitely stay there again and he has other CUTE listings in the area. Other dog friendly reviews: 
➡ My Place in Bozeman, MT was good. Nothing fancy but CLEAN. 
🚫 Baymont Inn - Moses Lake, WA - We DO NOT recommend. Yes, it is dog friendly but it was old, tired and NOT Clean. 
4. Cowboy Cafe - Sheridan, WY - The staff is friendly and breakfast was delish. Make sure you check out the tee that I had to buy.

My girl and I have loads of stories from our trip but Washington locals might correlate our trip with the Gray Fire in Spokane, WA.  Driving back home was long and challenging.  On Saturday, we left Wyoming at 7:45 am and rolled into Moses Lake, WA at 11:30 pm. No lunch or dinner stops, we weren't hungry [good road trip snacks from Trader Joe's]. My girl was battling a migraine so I did most of the driving but when we were trying to get to Moses Lake which is west of Spokane off of I-90 we kept hitting highway and road closures. A big thank you to the police officer in Cheney, WA that gave us directions.  My girl was calm and navigated us out of that mess and even took over the last 2 hours of driving. My heart goes out to all the people that were impacted by the fires in Spokane.  There are still I-90 road closures. All the disasters that have been happening this month have been so unsettling. 

If you made it this far, thank you so much for stopping by!

My oldest brother is in town.  We were originally supposed to be in Maui right now. Our trip has been postponed.  My thoughts are with the everyone that has been impacted by the fires.

This is when I tell you that my Momma and I are staying in Airbnb's and my brother is sleeping in the van.  He's customizing his own van so this has been a good way for him to figure out what works and what doesn't.  We've been thoroughly enjoying ourselves.  The coast is gorgeous and the weather has been perfect.
